message.content:
Reinforcement Learning, Probabilistic Methods, Neural Networks. 

Reinforcement Learning is the main focus of the paper, as the authors use it to study multiagent learning in simulated soccer. They compare two reinforcement learning algorithms: TD-Q learning with linear neural networks and Probabilistic Incremental Program Evolution (PIPE). 

Probabilistic Methods are also used in the PIPE algorithm, which uses adaptive "probabilistic prototype trees" to synthesize programs that calculate action probabilities from current inputs. 

Neural Networks are used in the TD-Q algorithm, which uses linear neural networks as evaluation functions (EFs) to map input/action pairs to expected reward.
